# Technical Context: Narva Website

## Technologies Used
- **Frontend**: HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript
- **Styling**: CSS Grid, Flexbox for responsive layouts
- **Assets**: Compressed images (.jpg format)
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages
- **Version Control**: Git/GitHub

## Development Setup
- **Local Development**: Any web browser for testing
- **Asset Organization**: `/assets/compress-images/` directory
- **Code Structure**: Separate HTML, CSS, JS files
- **Image Assets**: Pre-compressed product images available

## Technical Constraints
- **No Backend**: Static website only
- **No Frameworks**: Pure HTML/CSS/JS (no React, Vue, etc.)
- **No Build Process**: Direct file serving
- **No Database**: All content hardcoded in HTML/JS
- **Cross-Browser**: Support for modern browsers

## Dependencies
- **None**: No external libraries or frameworks
- **Fonts**: Google Fonts or web-safe fonts
- **Images**: Local asset files only
- **Icons**: CSS-based or SVG icons preferred

## Performance Considerations
- **Image Optimization**: Use compressed images from assets folder
- **CSS Organization**: Modular CSS structure
- **JavaScript**: Minimal JS for interactions
- **Loading**: Optimize for fast initial page load

## Browser Support
- **Modern Browsers**: Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- **Mobile Browsers**: iOS Safari, Chrome Mobile
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach
- **Progressive Enhancement**: Basic functionality without JS

## Future Technical Considerations
- **E-commerce Integration**: External links to shopping platforms
- **CMS Integration**: Potential future content management
- **Analytics**: Google Analytics integration capability
- **SEO**: Meta tags and semantic HTML structure